  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Security Program with Adventist Development and Relief Agency (ADRA) - Mozambique - 2017</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the north central region of Mozambique, ADRA supports the Munguluni Adventist Mission School Project located in the Zambezia province. It aims to develop self-sustaining institutions that provide a comprehensive education to the community. Rise Against Hunger meals incentivize students to attend school, with the enrollment of students jumping from 189 in 2014 to 460 in 2016 at the Munguluni Adventist Mission School. The project also integrates an agricultural program for self-sufficiency and builds local infrastructure to holistically improve the community.</narrative>
  </description>
